---
body_class: schedule
title: Schedule
---
= wrapped :article do
  %header
    %h2 Schedule

  .schedules
    %ul.legend
      - (8..22).step(0.5) do |hour|
        %li
          = float_to_time hour

    %ul.days
      - %w(Friday).each do |day|
        %li(class="#{day.downcase}")
          %strong= day
          %ul
            - schedule_for data.schedule[day.downcase], :start => 8 do |item, duration, distance|
              - style = "height: #{duration * 2 - 1}px; top: #{distance * 2}px"
              - title = "#{"%0.2f" % item.start}: #{item.title}"

              %li(class="#{item.type}" style="#{style}" title="#{title}")
                %span
                  %span= "%0.2f" % item.start
                  %strong= item.title

  %p
    Friday daytime comprises multiple tracks at eurucamp, of which JRubyConf EU
    is considered
    = succeed '.' do
      = link_to 'one track', 'http://2012.eurucamp.org/schedule'

  %h3 Saturday and Sunday
  %p
    If youâ€™re joining us on Saturday and Sunday for the eurucamp main sessions,
    = succeed '.' do
      = link_to 'check the eurucamp schedule', 'http://2012.eurucamp.org/schedule'
